    <updated>2024-10-01T11:18:53.288000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>pieterjanssens</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/68447</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;When the user navigates to "Open Task" and the task is configured to show details in a Web Dynpro ABAP application then the backend system generates a URL pointing to that backend system directly. For a seamless experience, it not only requires that backend to be exposed on the internet (with or without a gateway system), but also requires SAML2 to be setup. It defeats the purpose of Work Zone being the internet facing portal making backend applications accessible via the SAP Cloud Connector.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Is there a solution offered by SAP that allows the Open Task action to lead to a URL that is accessible within Work Zone itself?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Similar question here from a while back, but in the context of the Fiori Launchpad service with no solution: &lt;A href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/fiori-inbox-cloud-default-webgui-wda/qaq-p/12514253" target="_blank"&gt;https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/fiori-inbox-cloud-default-webgui-wda/qaq-p/12514253&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I hope it's supported. If it's not, then I plan to explore enhancing the class that generates the URL and return a link to WZ targetting the Shell-startWDA intent.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/work-zone-my-inbox-task-center-solution-to-get-open-task-to-generate-a-url/qaq-p/13884188"/>
    <published>2024-10-01T11:18:53.288000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
